<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 676 
                    The Chief of the Division of African Affairs (
                        Villard
                    ) to the Acting Secretary of
                            State
                    
                    Sent over the signature of Caffery. The gist of this message was
                        included in telegram No. 35 of July 16 from Grew to Byrnes (file
                        No. 800.00 Summaries/7–1645).</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d676</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">676</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-13T14:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-13T14:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-13T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-13T14:00:00-05:00" n="676" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/7–1345: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 676 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Division of African Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_VHS1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Villard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d676fn1">Sent over the signature of <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Caffery</persName>. The gist of this message was
                        included in telegram No. 35 of July 16 from <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> (file
                        No. 800.00 Summaries/7–1645).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-13T21:00:00+02:00">July 13, 1945—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4225. From <persName corresp="#p_VHS1">Villard</persName>.</p>
                <p>… With reference London’s 6984 July 11 to <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>,<note n="2" xml:id="d676fn2">
                        <ref target="#d673">Document No. 673</ref>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_PC1">Peake</persName> reaffirms intention of British
                    government not to raise at Berlin any question concerning extent of Russian
                    participation which is accepted in principle role [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>]
                    subject of any discussion concerning Tangier between British and Russians being
                    envisaged as limited to deal by which British would obtain something in exchange
                    for Russian admission to conversations. British believe French will accept
                    postponement of conversations until first week August.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
